1.title: History in the Making
1.plot: Ryan and his West Coast crew forge a place in automotive history when they team up with living legend, Carroll Shelby, to build a one of a kind Mustang.

2.title: The Royal Rover
2.plot: West Coast Customs goes global when it transforms a standard Range Rover into a never before built concept car, the Range Stormer, for a member of the royal family in Dubai.

3.title: Habitat Truck
3.plot: After customizing cars for celebrities and the super wealthy, Ryan decides to give back to a worthy cause. He comes up with an idea to build the "Ultimate Contractor's Truck" for Habitat for Humanity, an organization that supplies affordable housing.

4.title: Shaquillac
4.plot: West Coast Customs reconnects with the client that put them on the map - basketball superstar Shaquille O'Neal. Ryan has built many cars for Shaq in the past and so it's time to take it to the next level to win Shaq's business back.

5.title: Asanti Mercedes
5.plot: Ryan teams up with custom wheel design company Asanti, to create a Mercedes Benz masterpiece for them to display at this year's SEMA Car Show. Rap superstar Snoop Dog drops in with a special request.

6.title: Dourdan Charger
6.plot: Gary Dourdan, star of the TV show CSI, cruises into West Coast Customs with a plan for his classic Dodge Charger that could be the biggest challenge the shop has ever faced.

1.title: '67 Barracuda
1.plot: Ryan Friedlinghuas, owner of West Coast Customs, is asked to customize a '67 Barracuda as a tribute to late Hot Rod designer Boyd Coddington. He hires Boyd's old shop manager, Duane to help out. But Duane's old school ways soon clash with Ryan's team.

2.title: Road to Sema
2.plot: Ryan and his crew head to Vegas for SEMA where WCC is the main event. The crew will teach students how to paint, wrap vinyl and fabricate stereos all while customizing 5 cars. But before they can head out the door, someone on the team delivers bad news.

3.title: Christian Audigier Hummer
3.plot: Ryan and his WCC crew race to customize a hummer for Christian Audigier, owner of designer clothing Ed Hardy. They have 30 days to turn a standard military hummer into a one-of-a-kind convertible for a photo shoot that will launch Christian's new line.

4.title: Jesse James Chevy Truck
4.plot: Ryan meets with his old friend Jesse James of West Coast Choppers about customizing his 1990 Chevy pick-up truck. Ryan decides to pitch in and get his hands dirty for this project, which catches everyone by surprise.

5.title: Zach and Cody's Xmas Cars
5.plot: Ryan and his crew customize a Subaru Impreza and a Mitsubishi Lancer for twins Dillon and Cole Sprouse, the teenage stars of "The Suite Life of Zach and Cody." Ryan gives the two vehicles the complete WCC makeover and surprise Christmas morning delivery

6.title: Monster Bentley
6.plot: Ryan and the crew are hired by Noel, the CEO of Monster Cables, to customize his Bentley. Noel wants a special lift designed to get his Segway into the trunk. The team gives the car a unique paint and upholstery job but struggles with fitting the lift.

7.title: Ultimate Taco Truck
7.plot: Chronic Tacos, a Southern California restaurant chain, needs a promotional vehicle for the grand opening of a new store. With the deadline only nine days away, when an employee goes MIA Ryan is forced to make a change in personnel.

8.title: Challenger Convertible
8.plot: Ryan and his West Coast crew turn a brand new 2009 Dodge Challenger into a convertible for a client from Las Vegas. Ryan heads to Germany to check in on his new WCC shop in Berlin but while he's away a key employee quits, blaming Rory's incompetence.

9.title: Escalade & Smart Car
9.plot: Paris Hilton comes to pick up a Bentley customized in vivid pink. Then, Biohazard lead vocalist, Evan Seinfeld and his wife Tera Patrick bring in their Escalade for a luxury limo conversion. Evan also asks Ryan to customize Tera's Smart Car for a V Day

10.title: 58 Chevy Nomad Wagon
10.plot: Ryan and his West Coast Customs crew give a '58 Chevy Nomad a complete makeover for NASCAR driver Rusty Wallace including the installation of a racing engine. But a request for an enormous moon roof throws a wrench into their build schedule.

11.title: GTO
11.plot: Ryan and his West Coast crew merge the body of a classic 1969 GTO onto the rolling chassis of a 2006 GTO for X Games Drifting Champion, Tanner Faust. Sean's patience wears thin as the shop gets dirtier and fists are ready to fly when tensions peak.

12.title: Stallone 55 Ford Truck
12.plot:

13.title: Vans Van
13.plot: When Ryan visits the Vans Headquarters to check out his customs shoe line, he's asked to customize a 1974 Mercedes van. The van's unique see through poly-cast roof proves to be a huge challenge to fabricate, especially when it cracks during assembly.

14.title: 2007 Maybach
14.plot: Two members of the San Manuel Native American tribe of Southern California, bring their $350,000 Maybach to West Coast Customs in the hopes that Ryan can add his special WCC touch. Then Ryan is asked to work on a special project by a very unique client.

15.title: Wrench Rod
15.plot: Ryan and his West Coast Customs crew customize an old '37 Model A Ford, going old school turning a clunker into a classic Hot Rod to help promote Ryan and his wife Meagan's new line of clothing, "Wrench."

16.title: Lamborghini
16.plot: Ryan and his crew give the WCC makeover to a Lamborghini and transform it into the ultimate eye catching speed machine. Ryan learns how to flame a car when a donor of the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles asks him to work on a special project.

5.title: Stallone's '55 Ford
5.plot: Sylvester Stallone asks Ryan to customize '55 Ford truck for an action film that he is directing and starring in. Sly needs three identical versions of the truck to be used in the film, prompting Ryan to call in reinforcements from Rory's alma mater.

imdb.plot outline: STREET CUSTOMS, the popular series that chronicles Ryan Friedlinghaus and the rest of the famed West Coast Customs crew as they transform ordinary cars into masterpieces, is back with four new episodes. Ryan and West Coast Customs remain at the top of their game, customizing such rare cars as a $350,000 Maybach and a '37 Model A Ford. But cars aren't the only thing on Ryan's mind in the new episodes. With his two clothing and shoe lines, a special project for charity and a visit from a very unique client, there's never a dull moment at WCC.
